The paper focuses on developing a parallel algorithm for computing pairwise association measures, specifically Kendall's tau coefficient, on Intel Xeon Phis. This involves optimizing sorting algorithms using SIMD vector instructions and workload balancing. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computer Engineering (cs.CE), Databases (cs.DB), and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories.
